This file describes the use of initng_event_send()

Fist, define your event struct:

	typedef struct {
		s_event_type *event_type;
		int something;
	} s_some_event;


The event_type element is mandatory, and must be the first.

Set-up an event:

	s_some_event my_event;

	my_event->event_type = &STRANGE_EVENT;
	my_event->something = 5;


Then you can send it:

	initng_event_send((s_event *) &my_event);

